据韩国中央防疫对策本部24日通报，截至当天上午9时，韩国较前一天下午4时新增161例新冠肺炎确诊病例，累计确诊病例达763例，出现7例死亡病例。
As of 9: 00 a.m. on the same day, the Republic of Korea had 161 new cases of confirmed cases of New Crown Pneumonia, with a cumulative total of 763 confirmed cases and 7 deaths, the ministry said.
另据韩媒报道，一名16个月的女婴被确诊感染，这是目前韩国年龄最小的新冠肺炎确诊病例。
A 16-month-old girl was diagnosed with the infection, the youngest confirmed case of pneumonia in South Korea, the media reported.
随着新冠肺炎疫情在韩国蔓延，韩国总统文在寅23日下午宣布，决定将新冠肺炎传染病危机预警级别上调至最高的“严重”级别，大幅强化防疫应对体系。
With the outbreak of pneumonia in South Korea, South Korean President Wen Jiabao announced the afternoon of 23, decided to raise the alert level of the new crown pneumonia infectious disease crisis to the highest "serious" level, significantly strengthen the epidemic prevention response system.
11名军人确诊！7700名军人被隔离据韩联社报道，韩国国防部称，截至24日一早，共有11名军人感染新型冠状病毒肺炎，为阻止疫情进一步扩散到军营，超7700名军人被隔离。
Eleven servicemen were quarantined as early as Monday, 11 soldiers were infected with the new coronavirus pneumonia, and more than 7,700 were quarantined to stop the outbreak spreading to military barracks, the newspaper reported.
国防部称，2月23日，韩国军方数据显示有7人确认，而截至24日上午8点这一数字上升为11，其中陆军有8人确诊，海军、空军及海军陆战队各1人确诊。
On February 23, South Korean military data showed seven people confirmed, while the figure rose to 11 by 8 a.m. Thursday, with eight Army personnel confirmed and one Navy, Air Force and Marine Corps confirmed, the Defense Ministry said.
据一名军官称，4名新增确诊士兵疑似与营房内的确诊患者接触后感染病毒。
According to an officer, four of the newly identified soldiers were suspected of contracting the virus following contact with confirmed patients in the barracks.
韩国军方21日报告第一起确诊病例。
The South Korean military reported the first confirmed case on the 21st.
据官方通报，目前韩国大部分确诊患病例集中在大邱以及庆尚北道地区。
The majority of confirmed cases in South Korea are in Daegu and Gyeongshan North Province, officials said.
首尔市政府24日召开紧急会议，要求警察局配合政府工作，限制集会严防疫情扩散；同时称每日将定时通报疫情，临时关闭诸多公共设施，25个保健中心停止一般医疗服务、24小时运营“筛查诊所”等。
Seoul 24 emergency meeting, asked the police to work with the government to limit the spread of the epidemic, said the epidemic will be notified on a daily basis, temporary closure of a number of public facilities, 25 health centres stopped general medical services, 24-hour "screening clinics," and so on.
首尔市市长朴元淳表示，面对疫情的严峻形势，首尔要采取“先发制人”的有力措施，已建立应急响应机制，正将部分医院改建或增设可隔离使用的病房，确保医疗资源。
Seoul needs to take "pre-emptive" measures in the face of the severe situation, said Park Yuanchun, mayor of Seoul. Emergency response mechanisms have been put in place and some hospitals are being renovated or added to separate wards to ensure medical resources.
女主持上班发烧被送医院：节目紧急停播据韩联社报道，23日，韩国JTBC电视台气象女主持金敏娥因发低烧被送往医院，并接受新冠肺炎病毒检测。
Woman host sent to hospital with fever: report Korean television broadcaster JTBC Meteorologist Kim Myin-e was taken to hospital with a low fever and tested for the virus, Kyodo news agency reported.
目前已自我隔离，其参与录制的新闻节目《早间&》也在24日被紧急停播。
Now self-segregated, its news program, Morning & amp; amp; amp; P, was also suspended on the 24th.
JTBC电视台方面还表示，为以防万一，《早间&》节目组的全部成员，目前也都自我隔离。
JTBC also said that all of its members, as a precaution, are now self-segregated.
“电视台从业者活动范围广，接触人员多，这都是迫不得已的措施”。
"The wide range of activities of television operators and the large number of contacts are measures of last resort," he said.
韩国上调新冠肺炎疫情预警至最高级别延迟开学日期据新华社消息，韩国总统文在寅23日下午宣布，政府根据传染病专家的建议，决定将新冠肺炎传染病危机预警级别上调至最高的“严重”级别，大幅强化防疫应对体系。
South Korea raises alert for pneumonia due to SARS At the highest level, South Korean President Wen Jiabao announced Tuesday afternoon that the government, on the advice of infectious disease experts, decided to raise the alert level of the New Crown Pneumonia infectious disease crisis to the highest "serious" level and substantially strengthen the epidemic prevention and treatment system, Xinhua reported.
文在寅表示，现在韩国新冠疫情形势面临“重大分水岭”，未来几天是重要关头，政府要采取“史无前例的强力应对措施”。
Wen said the situation of the new crown in South Korea now faces a "major watershed" and that the next few days are critical for the government to take "an unprecedented and forceful response."
他说，韩国政府要继续保持以疾病管理本部为中心的防疫体系，同时强化总理主持的中央灾难安全对策本部的作用，加强政府各部门的应对，进一步增加中央对地方政府的支援。
He said the government will continue to maintain an epidemic prevention system centred on the headquarters of disease management, while strengthening the role of the central disaster safety response headquarters chaired by the Prime Minister, strengthening the response of government departments and further increasing central support to local governments.
韩国的传染病预警分为“关注”“注意”“警戒”“严重”四个级别。
The early warning of infectious diseases in Korea is divided into four levels: concern, attention, vigilance and severity.
在发布“严重”预警之后，政府可采取最高级别的应对措施，包括下令各级学校停课、禁止集体活动等。
After issuing a "serious" warning, the government could respond at the highest level, including ordering schools to suspend classes at all levels and banning group activities.
韩国政府23日决定，将全国幼儿园、中小学等各级学校2020学年的开学日期延期一周，从3月2日推迟至3月9日。
The government decided Wednesday to postpone the start of the 2020 school year in kindergartens, schools and other schools by one week, from March 2 to March 9.
韩国教育部：对本学期休学的留学生放宽学分限制2月24日，中国驻韩使馆提醒在韩留学的中国学生：①入境前：务必同韩国就读院校联系；②入境时：23日至29日被确定为“集中管理周”，中国留学生须按特别入境程序确认健康状况，并在手机安装“自我诊断应用程序（专用app）”；③入境后：自我隔离14日，通过专用app配合学校每日一报。
The Chinese Embassy in South Korea reminded Chinese students studying in South Korea on Feb. 24 that they must contact their Korean counterparts before entering the country. When entering the country, they must contact their Korean counterparts during the "Central Management Week."
④韩教育部表示，将面向对本学期休学的留学生放宽学分限制，同时，鼓励各高校签署互认学分协议，方便中国学生在华期间网上选修其他学校的课程获取学分。
The ministry said it would relax credit limits for students suspended from school this term and encourage universities to sign mutual credit recognition agreements to make it easier for Chinese students to earn credits by taking courses from other schools online while in China.
15个国家和地区对韩国实施入境管制韩联社消息称，韩国外交部24日表示，随着新型冠状病毒（COVID-19）疫情在韩国蔓延，越来越多的国家和地区对韩国实施入境管制，进一步加大检疫力度。
South Korea's foreign ministry said Thursday that more and more countries and regions have imposed immigration controls on South Korea to further strengthen quarantine as the new coronavirus (COVID-19) epidemic spreads in South Korea, the Foreign Ministry said Thursday.
截至目前，禁止来自韩国的人员入境或加强入境管理措施的国家和地区共15个。
So far, a total of 15 countries and territories have prohibited the entry of persons from the Republic of Korea or strengthened immigration control measures.
以色列、巴林、约旦、基里巴斯、萨摩亚、美属萨摩亚6个国家禁止14天内访问过韩国的外国人入境，或只允许在无疫区停留14天并接受健康检查的人员入境。
Six countries -- Israel, Bahrain, Jordan, Kiribati, Samoa and American Samoa -- prohibited the entry of foreigners who had visited the Republic of Korea within 14 days, or allowed entry only to those who stayed in a no-epidemic area for 14 days and underwent health checks.
中国驻韩使馆提醒在韩中国公民加强自我防护中国驻韩使馆今天发布公告，公告称，韩政府已将新冠肺炎疫情预警上调至最高级别“严重”，并将大邱和庆尚北道地区划为“特别管控区”。
Chinese Embassy reminds Chinese citizens in South Korea to step up self-defense China's embassy in South Korea said in a statement today that the South Korean government has raised its early warning of the outbreak of pneumonia to the highest level and has designated Daegu and Gyeongshan North Province as "special control areas."
韩政府将加大应对力度，可视情采取包括下令关闭学校、禁止集会等措施。
The South Korean government will step up its response, including by ordering the closure of schools and banning assemblies, as appropriate.
中国驻韩国大使馆提醒广大在韩中国公民：①避免前往人群密集地区及韩方指定的特别管控区。
The Chinese Embassy reminds Chinese citizens in South Korea to "avoid going to densely populated areas and special control areas designated by the ROK."
出门佩戴口罩，勤洗手，勤消毒，勤通风。
Wear a mask, wash your hands frequently, disinfect frequently and ventilate frequently.
②如出现发热等疑似症状，应避免外出或同他人接触，及时拨打韩国疾病管理本部电话1339（有中文服务）接受诊察治疗。
"If fever and other suspected symptoms, should avoid going out or contact with others, timely call Korea Department of Disease Control telephone 1339 (Chinese service) for consultation and treatment.
③建议各侨团取消集会、聚餐等大型活动。
Overseas Chinese delegations are advised to cancel gatherings, meals and other large-scale activities.
④科学应对、积极预防、避免恐慌，不信谣、不传谣。
Respond scientifically, actively prevent, avoid panic, and do not believe or spread rumors.
